    </p>
    <p>
        <br><b>7. Cookies</b><br>
        a) General<br>
        We do not pass on your data to third parties without a legal basis. We also do not pass on your data to third countries unless you are in a third country or the processing of contracts requires the transfer of your data to a third country. In order to make visiting our website attractive and to enable the use of certain functions, we use so-called cookies on various pages. These are small text files that are stored on your terminal device. Some of the cookies we use are deleted after the end of the browser session, i.e. after closing your browser (so-called session cookies). Other cookies remain on your end device and enable us or our partner companies to recognize your browser during your next visit (persistent cookies). We use cookies to personalise content and advertisements and to analyse access to our website. We also share information about your use of our site with our social media, advertising and analytics partners. Details can be found at: http://www.google.com/intl/de/policies/privacy/partners/.<br><br>
        b) Legal base<br>
        At this moment we are using cookies on the basis of Art. 6 Para. 1 lit. f) DSGVO as legal basis. As described above, we have legitimate interests in the use of cookies and the use of cookies is necessary to achieve these interests (for example, legitimate interest in analyzing user behavior to optimize both our Web site and our advertising). We have examined whether the predominant interests of visitors to our website are opposed to the use of cookies, but in the overall view we have come to the conclusion that this is not the case.<br><br>
    </p>
    <p>
        <br><b>8. Google Analytics</b><br>
